HEADWORD: Opelet
<hw>Ope"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
bright-colored European actinian (<spn>Anemonia sulcata</spn>, syn.
<spn>Anthea sulcata</spn>); -- so called because it does not retract its
tentacles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

